'''人权战线'''（英语：'''H'''uman '''R'''ights '''C'''ampaign，缩写HRC）是美国最大的[[LGBT|LGBT]]民事权利倡导团体和政治游说组织。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.cnn.com/2007-08-10/politics/gay.forum_1_lesbian-couples-gay-issues-human-rights-campaign-foundation?_s=PM:POLITICS|title=Democratic hopefuls pressed on gay issues at forum – CNN|date=2007-08-10|work=[[CNN|CNN]]|accessdate=2011-02-24|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101017030019/http://articles.cnn.com/2007-08-10/politics/gay.forum_1_lesbian-couples-gay-issues-human-rights-campaign-foundation?_s=PM%3APOLITICS|archivedate=2010-10-17}}</ref>

==组织结构==
人权战线是两个单独的的[[非营利组织|非营利组织]]和一个[[政治行动委员会|政治行动委员会]]的联盟组织。第一个非营利组织是是人权战线基金会，一个聚焦于研究、倡导和教育的[[501(c)|501(c)]](3)组织。<ref>{{cite web|title=HRC Foundation|url=http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/hrc-foundation|work=hrc.org|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|accessdate=2012-08-24|archive-date=2015-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151122030243/http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/hrc-foundation|dead-url=no}}</ref>第二个非营利组织是人权战线，同样是一个501(c)(4)组织。<ref>{{cite web|title=Frequently Asked Questions|url=http://www.hrc.org/support/frequently-asked-questions|work=hrc.org|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|accessdate=2012-08-24|archive-date=2020-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805212938/https://www.hrc.org/support/frequently-asked-questions/|dead-url=no}}</ref>它通过游说国家和州的官和国会员赞同支持LGBT的法案，或者动员其成员参与草根运动，聚焦于促进[[女同性恋|女同性恋]]、[[男同性恋|男同性恋]]、[[双性恋|双性恋]]和[[跨性别|跨性别]]（LGBT）人群的社会福利。最后一个是人权战线政治行动委员会，旨在支持那些拥护该委员会的关于[[LGBT权益|LGBT权益]]的立场的候选人。<ref name=structure>{{cite web|title=Human Rights Campaign Foundation|url=http://www.guidestar.org/PartnerReport.aspx?partner=justgivews&ein=52-1481896|work=guidestar.org|publisher=[[GuideStar|GuideStar]]|accessdate=2012-08-24|archive-date=2020-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323184137/http://www.guidestar.org/PartnerReport.aspx?partner=justgivews&ein=52-1481896|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=mission>{{cite web|title=Mission Statement|url=http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/mission-statement|work=hrc.org|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|accessdate=2012-08-24|archive-date=2015-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151011083233/http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/mission-statement|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===领导人员===
人权战线的领导人员包括主席{{link-en|查得·格里芬|Chad Griffin}}。<ref>{{cite news|last=Harmon|first=Andrew|title=Chad Griffin Named President of HRC|url=http://www.advocate.com/News/Daily_News/2012/03/02/Chad_Griffin_Named_President_of_HRC/|accessdate=2012-03-02|newspaper=[[The_Advocate|The Advocate]]|date=2012-03-02|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120304075113/http://www.advocate.com/News/Daily_News/2012/03/02/Chad_Griffin_Named_President_of_HRC/|archivedate=2012-03-04}}</ref> 人权战线的工作由以下三个董事会支持：指导委员会，该组织的主管部门；人权战线基金会的董事会，掌管基金会的财政并制定基金会的官方政策；理事会，掌管从地方到全国的组织。这三个董事会都是由来自全国的志愿者构成的。<ref name=steeringcommittee>{{cite web|title=What is a Steering Committee?|url=http://www.hrc.org/blog/entry/what-is-a-steering-committee|work=hrc.org|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|accessdate=2012-08-24|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120824012124/http://www.hrc.org/blog/entry/what-is-a-steering-committee|archivedate=2012-08-24}}</ref>

==工作==
人权战线的优先任务包括：[[仇恨罪行|仇恨罪行]]和[[艾滋病|艾滋病]]的预防；促进同性伴侣的医疗福利、[[婚姻|婚姻]]和[[收养|收养]]权利；为联邦的{{link-en|《禁止就业歧视法案》|Employment Non-Discrimination Act}}和反[[性别认同|性别认同]]歧视的法律游说；反对校内{{link-en|殴打同性恋者|gay bashing}}的行为；以及与[[异性恋同盟|异性恋同盟]]、族群、宗教领袖和青年人建立联系。<ref name=issues>{{cite web|title=Issues: Human Rights Campaign|url=http://www.hrc.org/issues|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|accessdate=2012-02-21|archive-date=2014-06-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140606033323/http://www.hrc.org/issues|dead-url=no}}</ref>

人权战线基金会为不同的领域提供教育资源和出版服务，包括[[出柜|出柜]]、跨性别议题、LGBT相关医疗话题，也为LGBT人群面临的工作场所问题提供信息，特别是“{{link-en|企业平等指数|Corporate Equality Index}}”。该组织同样维护许多资源，包括LGBT父母养育、宗教和信仰议题、外来移民和青年发展协助。<ref name="Human Rights Campaign Foundation">{{Cite web |url=http://www.hrc.org/resources |title=Resources |accessdate=2015-06-19 |archive-date=2021-02-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210212010741/https://www.hrc.org/resources |dead-url=no }}</ref>

人权战线基金会的“出柜”项目为那些正在出柜的人提供信息。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hrc.org/resources/category/coming-out |title=Resources: Coming Out |accessdate=2015-06-19 |archive-date=2015-11-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151113043737/http://www.hrc.org/resources/category/coming-out |dead-url=no }}</ref>

人权战线为了仇恨罪行的法律和反歧视游说，并且为努力使{{link-en|马修·谢巴德和詹姆斯·伯德，Jr.预防仇恨犯罪法案|Matthew Shepard and James Byrd, Jr. Hate Crimes Prevention Act}}获得通过，以扩展联邦的仇恨罪法律，允许[[美国司法部|美国司法部]]调查并控告起因为被害人的实际或被感知的性别、[[性取向|性取向]]、性别认同或残疾。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hrc.org/sites/loveconquershate/about.asp |title=HRC: Matthew Shepard Act |accessdate=2015-06-19 |archive-date=2014-02-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228000707/http://www.hrc.org/sites/loveconquershate/about.asp |dead-url=no }}</ref>人权战线前主席{{link-en|乔·索尔蒙内赛|Joe Solmonese}}认为这项法律是“历史的里程碑”，该法律的通过标志着“我们作为一个国家首次明确地在法律中保护LGBT社群。”<ref name="President Barack Obama Signs Hate Crimes Legislation Into Law">{{Cite web |url=http://www.hrc.org/press-releases/entry/president-barack-obama-signs-hate-crimes-legislation-into-law |title=President Barack Obama Signs Hate Crimes Legislation Into Law |accessdate=2015-06-19 |archive-date=2013-05-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130522182227/http://www.hrc.org/press-releases/entry/president-barack-obama-signs-hate-crimes-legislation-into-law |dead-url=no }}</ref>

该组织在健康议题的工作传统上聚焦于响应艾滋病和HIV病毒的流行。近年来，人权战线已经为LGBT雇员、患者和他们的家庭处理了医疗环境中的歧视问题。自从2007年起，人权战线基金会已经发表了“医疗平等指数”，来评价医院的诸多问题，比如患者和雇员反歧视政策、雇员{{link-en|文化能力|cultural competence}}培训和医院的LGBT患者的家庭的探视权。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hrc.org/resources/entry/healthcare-equality-index-2011 |title=Resources: Healthcare Equality Index |accessdate=2015-06-19 |archive-date=2012-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120618031050/http://www.hrc.org/resources/entry/healthcare-equality-index-2011 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 自2013年起，在旧金山的加利福尼亚大学是美国唯一一个达到该指数满分的机构。<ref>{{cite web |publisher=Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality |url=https://innovations.ahrq.gov/profiles/inclusive-policies-communication-protocols-and-ongoing-training-lead-culturally-competent |title=Inclusive Policies, Communication Protocols and Ongoing Training Lead to Culturally Competent Care for Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, and Transgender Patients |date=2013-09-11 |accessdate=2013-09-18 |archive-date=2020-09-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922055822/https://innovations.ahrq.gov/profiles/inclusive-policies-communication-protocols-and-ongoing-training-lead-culturally-competent |dead-url=no }}</ref>人权战线的游说者和奥巴马政府一起，扩大医院的同性伴侣探视权。<ref name="Obama extends hospital visitation rights to same-sex partners of gays">{{cite news | url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/04/15/AR2010041505502.html | work=The Washington Post | first=Michael D. | last=Shear | title=Obama extends hospital visitation rights to same-sex partners of gays | date=2010-04-16 | accessdate=2015-06-19 | archive-date=2021-02-14 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210214002339/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/04/15/AR2010041505502.html | dead-url=no }}</ref> 2012年，人权战线宣布了影响广泛的“健康与衰老项目”的成立。该项目应对所有美国LGBT人群的健康问题和老年LGBT人群面临的特别挑战，包括歧视、虐待和孤独。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hrc.org/press-releases/entry/human-rights-campaign-foundation-expands-the-net-of-lgbt-healthcare-equalit|title=Human Rights Campaign Foundation Expands the Net of LGBT Healthcare Equality|date=2012-09-12|accessdate=2013-03-08|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924045706/http://www.hrc.org/press-releases/entry/human-rights-campaign-foundation-expands-the-net-of-lgbt-healthcare-equalit|dead-url=no}}</ref>

人权战线为废除“[[不问，不说|不问，不说]]”法律广泛地进行游说。该法律禁止男同性恋和女同性恋者在美国军队中公开自己的性取向。{{link-en|埃里克·阿尔瓦|Eric Alva}}是一名同性恋美国海军陆战队士兵，他是第一个在[[伊拉克战争|伊拉克战争]]中受伤的美国士兵。自此以后，他成为了代表人权战线的发言人来废除这项法律，并被邀请在签署仪式上站在总统[[贝拉克·奥巴马|贝拉克·奥巴马]]的身后。<ref name="Obama signs DADT repeal before big, emotional crowd">{{cite news | url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/12/22/AR2010122201888.html | work=The Washington Post | first1=William | last1=Branigin | first2=Debbi | last2=Wilgoren | first3=Perry | last3=Bacon Jr | title=Obama signs DADT repeal before big, emotional crowd | date=2010-12-22 | accessdate=2015-06-19 | archive-date=2020-11-20 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201120034907/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/12/22/AR2010122201888.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

==历史==
[[Image:Human_Right_Campaign_headquarters.JPG|thumb]]的人权战线总部]]
{{link-en|史蒂夫·恩丁|Steve Endean}}曾在1978年成立的“{{link-en|同性恋权益全国游说组织|Gay Rights National Lobby}}”工作，之后于1980年建立人权战线基金政治行动委员会，来为支持同性恋者的国会竞选者筹集资金。1983年，在当时华盛顿重要的LGBT权益活动家{{link-en|维克·巴希尔|Vic Basile}}被选举为第一任执行董事。1986年10月，人权战线基金会作为一个非盈利组织宣告成立。除了其他方面，人权战线基金会为有同性恋、双性恋或跨性别的父母和/或儿童的家庭提供帮助，为需要的人提供医疗和寻求工作场所的平等。<ref name=Bailey-history /><ref>{{cite web|title=HRC Foundation|url=http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/hrc-foundation|accessdate=2015-04-01|archive-date=2015-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151122030243/http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/hrc-foundation|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

1989年1月，巴希尔宣布离任。人权战线对其政治行动委员会的功能进行扩展，新加入了游说、研究、教育和媒体推广。<ref name=HRCJournal-history>{{cite journal|last=Birch|first=Elizabeth|title=The Human Rights Campaign: So Much More Than a Fund.|year=HRC Quarterly (Fall 1995)|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|pages=2–3|url=http://www.glbtq.com/social-sciences/human_rights_campaign.html|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120213150637/http://www.glbtq.com/social-sciences/human_rights_campaign.html|archivedate=2012-02-13|journal=|access-date=2015-06-19}}</ref>人权战线确定了一个新的“目的声明”：

{{cquote|为提升男女同性恋社群的社会福利，我们在联邦、州和地方的层面起草、支持和影响立法与政策。}}

{{link-en|蒂姆·麦克菲利|Tim McFeeley}}毕业于[[哈佛法学院|哈佛法学院]]，是波士顿同性恋者政治联盟的建立者，也是[[新英格兰|新英格兰]]人权战线委员会的共同主席。他被选举为新执行董事。在那时，所有的会员人数约为25000。<ref name=Bailey-history>{{cite book|last=Bailey|first=Mark|title="Human Rights Campaign." Gay Histories and Cultures|year=2000|publisher=Garland|location=New York|url=http://www.glbtq.com/social-sciences/human_rights_campaign.html|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120213150637/http://www.glbtq.com/social-sciences/human_rights_campaign.html|archivedate=2012-02-13|access-date=2015-06-19}}</ref>

1992年，人权战线第一次赞同了一位总统候选者，[[比尔·克林顿|比尔·克林顿]]。1993年3月，人权战线启动了一个新项目，叫做“[[国家出柜日|国家出柜日]]”。自1995年1月至2004年1月，{{link-en|伊丽莎白·伯奇|Elizabeth Birch}}担任人权战线的执行董事。在她的领导下，人权战线的会员数量翻了四倍多，达到五十万。<ref>{{cite web|last=Althafer|first=Emily|title=Leading gay rights advocate to speak at UF|url=http://news.ufl.edu/2006/01/23/human-rights-talk/|publisher=University of Florida News: source: Adelisse Fontanet, xxx-1665 ext. 326|accessdate=2012-02-22|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060916211856/http://news.ufl.edu/2006/01/23/human-rights-talk/|archivedate=2006-09-16}}</ref>

1995年，这个组织删去了名字中的“基金”，更名为人权战线。同年，它进行了一次彻底的重组。人权战线基金会增加了新的项目，比如“工作场所项目”和“家庭项目”，人权战线也扩充了它的研究、交流、市场营销和公共关系的功能。该组织也揭幕了新的[[标志|标志]]，一个蓝色方框中有一个黄色平等标志。这已经成为了LGBT社群中辨识度最高的标志之一。<ref name="HRC Logo">{{cite web|title=The HRC Story: About Our Logo|url=http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/about-our-logo|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|accessdate=2012-02-22|archive-date=2015-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151112082857/http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/about-our-logo|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2002年，人权战线在[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿哥伦比亚特区]]购置了一处总部大楼。这个大楼位于罗德岛大道1640号，曾经是国际[[圣约之子会|圣约之子会]]的总部。人权战线重新装修了大楼并于2003年入驻。<ref name="The HRC Story: Our Building">{{cite web|title=The HRC Story: Our Building|url=http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/our-building|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|accessdate=2013-05-23|archive-date=2015-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151104160201/http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/our-building|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[Image:ChicagoGayPride2005_1.jpg|thumb]]

作为{{link-en|华盛顿千禧年大游行|llennium March on Washington}}的周边活动的一部分，人权战线基金会赞助了一场在华盛顿的{{link-en|肯尼迪纪念球场|Robert F. Kennedy Memorial Stadium}}举行的筹款音乐会，于2000年4月29日举行。这场音乐会被宣传为结束仇恨犯罪，“平等摇滚”纪念了仇恨罪的受害者和他们的家庭，比如演讲嘉宾丹尼斯和{{link-en|朱蒂·谢巴德|Judy Shepard}}，他们都是[[马修·谢巴德|马修·谢巴德]]的父母。超过45000人<ref name="concert-hate crimes">{{cite web|title=Resources: Hate Crimes Timeline|url=http://www.hrc.org/resources/entry/hate-crimes-timeline#2000|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|accessdate=2012-02-22|archive-date=2015-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117011740/http://www.hrc.org/resources/entry/hate-crimes-timeline#2000|dead-url=no}}</ref> 参加了这一活动，包括[[梅丽莎·埃瑟里奇|梅丽莎·埃瑟里奇]]、[[加斯·布鲁克斯|加斯·布鲁克斯]]、[[宠物店男孩|宠物店男孩]]、[[凯蒂莲|凯蒂莲]]、[[内森·雷恩|内森·雷恩]]、[[洛福斯·温莱特|洛福斯·温莱特]]、{{link-en|Albita Rodriguez|Albita Rodríguez}}和[[夏卡·康|夏卡·康]]。<ref>{{cite web|title=More Artists Added to Equality Rocks:  Michael Feinstein, Chaka Khan, Kathy Najimy and Rufus Wainwright Join Garth Brooks, Ellen DeGeneres, Melissa Etheridge, Anne Heche, Kristen Johnston, kd lang, Nathan Lane and Pet Shop Boys To Benefit the Human Rights Campaign Foundation|url=http://www.nyrock.com/worldbeat/04_2000/041200a.asp|publisher=nyrock.com World Beat|accessdate=2012-02-22|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121115095023/http://www.nyrock.com/worldbeat/04_2000/041200a.asp|archivedate=2012-11-15}}</ref>

伊丽莎白·伯奇的继任者是{{link-en|谢丽尔·雅克|Cheryl Jacques}}，她在担任执行董事后仅11个月就于2004年11月辞职。在人权战线发表的声明中，雅克说她辞职的原因是“管理理念上的分歧”。<ref name="Jacques Press Release">{{cite web|title=Cheryl Jacques to Leave Human Rights Campaign: HRC Boards Put Transition Plan in Place|url=http://www.hrc.org/press-releases/entry/cheryl-jacques-to-leave-human-rights-campaign|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|accessdate=2012-02-22|archive-date=2013-09-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130908235453/http://www.hrc.org/press-releases/entry/cheryl-jacques-to-leave-human-rights-campaign|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2005年3月，人权战线宣布任命乔·索尔蒙内赛为主席，把他描述为一个“有着无与伦比的历史成就，是国家的先驱强势候选者”，并且对“持有不同政治观点和意识形态的美国人”都有吸引力。<ref>{{cite news|title=Joe Solmonese Named Human Rights Campaign President: Leader with Unmatched Record to Embark on Heartland Tour during First Week on Job|url=http://www.hrc.org/press-releases/entry/joe-solmonese-named-human-rights-campaign-president|accessdate=2012-02-22|newspaper=Human Rights Campaign|date=2005-03-09|archive-date=2014-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228001822/http://www.hrc.org/press-releases/entry/joe-solmonese-named-human-rights-campaign-president|dead-url=no}}</ref>

人权战线在2005年发起了“宗教和信仰项目”以动员神职人员为LGBT人群呼吁倡导，帮助组建“哥伦比亚特区的神职人员为婚姻平等联合”来推动[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区同性婚姻|哥伦比亚特区同性婚姻]]的立法。<ref name="Fenty to sign same-sex marriage bill at church in NW D.C.">{{cite news | url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/12/17/AR2009121704330.html | work=The Washington Post | first=Nikita | last=Stewart | title=Fenty to sign same-sex marriage bill at church in NW D.C | date=2009-12-18 | accessdate=2015-06-19 | archive-date=2020-03-23 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323184351/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/12/17/AR2009121704330.html | dead-url=no }}</ref> 2010年3月10日，第一个在[[哥伦比亚特区|哥伦比亚特区]]被法律承认的同性婚姻的仪式在人权战线的总部举行。<ref name="First gay marriages in District performed">{{cite news | url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/03/09/AR2010030901904.html | work=The Washington Post | first1=Ann E. | last1=Marimow | first2=Keith L. | last2=Alexander | title=First gay marriages in District performed | date=2010-03-10 | accessdate=2015-06-19 | archive-date=2020-03-23 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323184359/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/03/09/AR2010030901904.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

2007年8月9日，人权战线和{{link-en|美国标志电视台|Logo TV}}共同为2008年民主党致力于LGBT议题的总统竞选人主持了一个论坛。<ref name="Dems Court the Gay Vote">{{Cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/GMA/Story?id=3466074&page=1 |title=Dems Court the Gay Vote |accessdate=2015-06-19 |archive-date=2016-04-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160416163337/http://abcnews.go.com/GMA/Story?id=3466074&page=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

人权战线在{{link-en|2008年大选|United States elections, 2008}}中的“获胜之年”的运动中耗资七百万美元，是该组织历史上最大规模的选举运动。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/our-victories |title=Our victo: Year to Win |accessdate=2015-06-19 |archive-date=2015-11-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151104194812/http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/our-victories |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="2008 election">{{cite web|title=Our Victories (Election Heavyweights section)|url=http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/our-victories|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|accessdate=2012-02-22|archive-date=2015-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151104194812/http://www.hrc.org/the-hrc-story/our-victories|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2010年，人权战线游说废除美国对于[[HIV|HIV]]感染者进入本国旅行或移民的禁令，表明需要“反对针对艾滋病的经常误导公共政策的污名和忽视”。<ref name="Ban Lifted">{{cite web|title=After 22 Years, HIV Travel and Immigration Ban Lifted|url=http://www.hrc.org/press-releases/entry/after-22-years-hiv-travel-and-immigration-ban-lifted|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|accessdate=2012-02-22|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924045652/http://www.hrc.org/press-releases/entry/after-22-years-hiv-travel-and-immigration-ban-lifted|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="After 22 years, HIV travel and immigration ban lifted">{{Cite web |url=http://miamiherald.typepad.com/gaysouthflorida/2010/01/hrc-after-22-years-hiv-travel-and-immigration-ban-lifted.html#ixzz0sxMtcovD |title=Miami Herald: After 22 years, HIV travel and immigration ban lifted |accessdate=2015-06-19 |archive-date=2020-08-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200813104809/https://miamiherald.typepad.com/gaysouthflorida/2010/01/hrc-after-22-years-hiv-travel-and-immigration-ban-lifted.html#ixzz0sxMtcovD |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2011年9月，索尔蒙内赛被宣布2012年合同到期后将不再担任主席。<ref>{{cite web|url = http://metroweekly.com/poliglot/2011/08/hrcs-solmonese-to-step-down.html|title = HRC's Solmonese to Step Down, Sources Say No Replacement Has Been Selected|author = Chris Geidner|date = August 27, 2011<!-- 3:20 AM-->|publisher = Metro Weekly|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120229055653/http://metroweekly.com/poliglot/2011/08/hrcs-solmonese-to-step-down.html|archivedate = 2012年2月29日|accessdate = 2015年6月19日}}</ref>尽管有人推测前亚特兰大地方议会主席{{link-en|凯茜·伍拉德|Cathy Woolard}}会被任命，然而2012年3月2日公布的继任者是“{{link-en|美国平权基金会|American Foundation for Equal Rights}}”的共同创始人查得·格里芬。他于2012年6月11日上任。<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.advocate.com/News/Daily_News/2012/03/02/Chad_Griffin_Named_President_of_HRC/|title = Chad Griffin Named President of HRC|date = March 2, 2012<!-- 10:59:03 am ET-->|author = Andrew Harmon|publisher = The Advocate|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120304075113/http://www.advocate.com/News/Daily_News/2012/03/02/Chad_Griffin_Named_President_of_HRC/|archivedate = 2012年3月4日|accessdate = 2015年6月19日}}</ref>

在2012年，人权战线执行了最大规模的动员行动，筹集捐献了两千万美元以支持奥巴马总统的连任，并促进婚姻平等和其它选举的重要事项。<ref>{{cite web|title=HRC 2012: Unprecedented Mobilization for Equality|url=http://www.hrc.org/election|accessdate=2013-03-08|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130202193611/http://www.hrc.org/election/|archivedate=2013-02-02}}</ref>大选之后的一天，华盛顿邮报强调人权战线的重要作用，在华盛顿、缅因州、马里兰州和明尼苏达州的婚姻平权以及塔米·鲍德温的竞选和奥巴马的连任竞选等事件中贡献卓著。<ref>{{cite news|title=Gay rights advocates welcome Election Day results for a change|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/decision2012/gay-rights-advocates-welcome-election-day-results-for-a-change/2012/11/07/66c48ab6-28a5-11e2-bab2-eda299503684_story.html|publisher=The Washington Post|accessdate=2013-03-08|first=Ned|last=Martel|date=2012-11-08|archive-date=2020-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323184437/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/decision2012/gay-rights-advocates-welcome-election-day-results-for-a-change/2012/11/07/66c48ab6-28a5-11e2-bab2-eda299503684_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2013年，人权战线组织了一个明信片运动，以支持《禁止就业歧视法案》。<ref>{{cite web|last1=Eilperin|first1=Juliet|title=Cindy McCain petitions husband to back gay rights bill|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2013/10/25/cindy-mccain-petitions-husband-to-back-gay-rights-bill/|publisher=The Washington Post|accessdate=2014-11-03|archive-date=2015-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150513213537/http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2013/10/25/cindy-mccain-petitions-husband-to-back-gay-rights-bill/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 阿拉斯加州的参议员[[丽莎·穆尔科斯基|丽莎·穆尔科斯基]]将这项运动归功于她支持该法案的投票。<ref name="#1">{{cite web|title=GOP Sen. Murkowski Credits HRC Postcard Campaign for her Pro-ENDA Vote|url=http://www.hrc.org/blog/entry/gop-sen.-murkowski-credits-hrc-postcard-campaign-for-her-pro-enda-vote|accessdate=2014-11-03|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924031843/http://www.hrc.org/blog/entry/gop-sen.-murkowski-credits-hrc-postcard-campaign-for-her-pro-enda-vote|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===年度资金筹集者===
自1997年起，人权战线每年举办一个全国的晚宴，邀请著名演讲者，是每年人权战线最大的单个资金筹集活动。2009年，总统贝拉克·奥巴马在人权战线第13次年度全国晚宴上向大约三千位来宾致辞。<ref name="#1"/>
奥巴马在他的演讲中重申了他废除“不问不说”法律和《[[捍卫婚姻法案|捍卫婚姻法案]]》并通过《禁止就业歧视法案》的承诺。<ref name="Huffington Post – Obama HRC Speech">{{Cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/10/10/obama-says-he-will-end-do_n_316524.html |title=Huffington Post – Obama HRC Speech |accessdate=2015-06-19 |archive-date=2016-02-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201203257/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/10/10/obama-says-he-will-end-do_n_316524.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>他同样在2011年发表了主旨演讲，重申他废除《捍卫婚姻法案》并通过《禁止就业歧视法案》，而且反对欺凌LGBT青年的承诺。其他历次晚宴上的重要演讲者包括[[比尔·克林顿|比尔·克林顿]]、[[马娅·安杰卢|马娅·安杰卢]]、{{link-en|Kweisi Mfume|Kweisi Mfume}}、[[乔·利伯曼|乔·利伯曼]]、[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]、{{link-en|理查德·盖法特|Dick Gephardt}}、{{link-en|约翰·路易斯|John Lewis (politician)}}、[[罗茜·奥唐纳|罗茜·奥唐纳]]、[[南希·佩洛西|南希·佩洛西]]、[[提姆·冈恩|提姆·冈恩]]、{{link-en|苏西·欧曼|Suze Orman}}、[[莎莉·菲尔德|莎莉·菲尔德]]、[[科里·布克|科里·布克]]和{{link-en|贝蒂·德杰尼勒斯|Betty DeGeneres}}。<ref name="previous dinners">{{cite web|title=About the Dinner: Previous Dinners|url=http://www.hrcnationaldinner.org/about/|publisher=hrcnationaldinner.org|accessdate=2012-02-22|archive-date=2020-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200810211459/https://hrcnationaldinner.org/about/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===人权战线的历史档案===
人权战线的历史档案自2004年起都被保存在[[康奈尔大学图书馆|康奈尔大学图书馆]]里。这些档案包括[[战略计划|战略计划]]文档、传真、会议记录、电子邮件、新闻稿、海报和竞选徽章。这些档案文件占用了2.4立方米（284立方英尺），名叫“人类的性取向收藏”，是这家图书馆“稀有的手稿收藏分部”中第二大的。2007年2月，这些档案文件对图书馆的学者开放，部分档案被安排在网上展示，叫做“25年的政治影响：人权战线的档案”。<ref>Lowery, George. (January 30, 2007) [http://www.news.cornell.edu/stories/Jan07/humanrightsrecords.gl.html 25 years of gay-rights struggles traced in online exhibit] {{Wayback|url=http://www.news.cornell.edu/stories/Jan07/humanrightsrecords.gl.html |date=20121109151823 }} ''[[The_Cornell_Chronicle|The Cornell Chronicle]]'' of [[Cornell_University|Cornell University]]. Retrieved July 29, 2007.</ref><ref>[[Cornell_University_Library|Cornell University Library]]. [http://rmc.library.cornell.edu/HRC/index.html 25 Years of Political Influence:The Records of the Human Rights Campaign] {{Wayback|url=http://rmc.library.cornell.edu/HRC/index.html |date=20191109012657 }} [[Cornell_University|Cornell University]]. Retrieved July 29, 2007.</ref>

